nsider.com%2Falzheimers-and-dementia-misconceptions-and-surprising-facts-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edementia%20or%20Alzheimer's%20diagnosis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20his%20symptoms%20do%20line%20up%20with%20mild%20cognitive%20impairment%2C%20which%20the%20National%20Institute%20on%20Aging%20characterizes%20by%20memory%20or%20thinking%20problems%20such%20as%20losing%20items%2C%20forgetting%20appointments%2C%20and%20having%20trouble%20remembering%20words%20or%20names.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20my%20dad's%20cognitive%20issues%20are%20clinically%20%26quot%3Bmild%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20still%20feel%20scary%20and%20concerning%20for%20my%20sisters%20and%20me.%20We%20know%20he%20is%20still%20capable%20of%20taking%20care%20of%20himself%2C%20but%20we%20still%20worry%20that%20his%20forgetfulness%20could%20put%20him%20in%20danger%20or%20lead%20to%20problems%20such%20as%20losing%20power%20because%20he%20forgot%20to%20pay%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20while%20our%20first%20instinct%20is%20to%20step%20in%20and%20take%20over%20things%2C%20my%20sisters%20and%20I%20also%20know%20that%20asserting%20too%20much%20control%20over%20our%20dad's%20life%20would%20threaten%20his%20independence%20and%20potentially%20cause%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%20So%20we've%20learned%20to%20strike%20a%20balance%20between%20letting%20him%20live%20his%20life%20while%20also%20being%20involved%20enough%20to%20ensure%20that%20he's%20safe%20and%20secure%2C%20both%20physically%20and%20financially.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271831131-1c6d-4fd0-9ba5-66eabde75794%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHere's%20what%20we're%20doing%20to%20help%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20helpful%20things%20we've%20done%20is%20accompanying%20our%20dad%20to%20his%20doctor's%20appointments.%20He%20lives%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhearing-loss-cochlea