.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F3-killed-in-lebanon-amid-protests-as-israeli-forces-remain-after-withdrawal-deadline%2Famp_articleshow%2F117575755.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2F3-killed-in-lebanon-amid-protests-as-israeli-forces-remain-after-withdrawal-deadline%2Famp_articleshow%2F117575755.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%201950%2C%20Ex-Indonesia%20President%20Attended%20Republic%20Day%20Parade%20At%20This%20Location%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EHuge%20tri-colour-themed%20banners%20have%20been%20put%20up%20along%20the%20Kartavya%20Path%20while%20the%20theme%20for%20this%20year's%20tableaux%20that%20would%20roll%20down%20the%20boulevard%20where%20the%20annual%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20take%20place%20is%20'Swarnim%20Bharat%3A%20Virasat%20aur%20Vikas'%2C%20focusing%20on%2075%20years%20of%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20maiden%20celebrations%20marking%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20India%20were%20not%20held%20on%20Rajpath%20(now%20Kartavya%20Path)%2C%20the%20historical%20avenue%20that%20has%20over%20time%20become%20synonymous%20with%20the%20ceremony.%20It%20was%20held%20in%20the%201930s-era%20Irwin%20Amphitheatre%20after%20the%20country%20got%20its%20first%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESukarno%2C%20the%20first%20president%20of%20Indonesia%2C%20was%20the%20chief%20guest%20at%20India's%20first%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20in%201950.%20And%2075%20years%20later%2C%20Indonesian%20President%20Prabowo%20Subianto%20will%20be%20the%20chief%20guest%20at%20this%20year's%20ceremonial%20parade%20which%20will%20also%20see%20the%20participation%20of%20a%20marching%20contingent%20and%20a%20band%20contingent%20from%20that%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIconic%20public%20buildings%2C%20parks%20and%20railway%20stations%20dazzled%20with%20lights%20on%20the%20night%20of%20January%2026%2C%201950%2C%20turning%20the%20capital%20city%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bfairyland%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFauji%20Akhbar%20(now%20Sainik%20Samachar)%2C%20in%20its%20February%204%20article%20'Birth%20of%20a%20Republic'%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20most%20solemn%20ceremony%2C%20held%20in%20the%20brilliantly%20lit%20and%20high%20domes%20of%20Durbar%20Hall%20at%20Government%20House%2C%20India%20was%20declared%20a%20Sovereign%20Democratic%20Republic%20exactly%20at%2018%20minutes%20past%2010%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20Thursday%2C%20January%2026%2C%201950.%20Six%20minutes%20later%2C%20Dr%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20president.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20birth%20of%20the%20Indian%20Republic%20and%20the%20installation%20of%20its%20first%20president%20were%20announced%20by%20a%20salute%20of%2031%20guns%20shortly%20after%2010%3A30%20am%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20impressive%20swearing-in%20ceremony%2C%20retiring%20Governor-General%20C%20Rajagopalachari%20read%20out%20the%20proclamation%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20%26quot%3BIndia%2C%20that%20is%2C%20Bharat%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20whereas%20it%20has%20been%20declared%20by%20the%20said%20Constitution%20that%20India%2C%20that%20is%2C%20Bharat%2C%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States%20comprising%20within%20the%20Union%20the%20territories%20which%20were%20hitherto%20the%20Governor's%20provinces%2C%20the%20Indian%20states%20and%20the%20Chief%20Commissioners'%20provinces%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20military%20journal%20had%20quoted%20the%20last%20Governor-General's%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20then%20took%20the%20oath%20and%20made%20a%20brief%20speech%2C%20first%20in%20Hindi%20and%20then%20in%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20our%20long%20and%20chequered%20history%20we%20find%20the%20whole%20of%20this%20vast%20land%20from%20Kashmir%20in%20the%20north%20to%20Cape%20Comorin%20in%20the%20South%2C%20from%20Kathiawad%20and%20Kutch%20in%20the%20west%20to%20Coconada%20and%20Kamrup%20in%20the%20east%2C%20brought%20together%20under%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20one%20Constitution%20and%20one%20Union%2C%20which%20takes%20over%20the%20responsibility%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20more%20than%20320%20million%20men%20and%20women%20that%20inhabit%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Prasad%20said%20in%20his%20historic%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20erupted%20in%20celebration%20soon%20after%20Prasad%20was%20sworn%20in%20as%20India's%20first%20President.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20elegant%20exposed-brick%20structure%20of%20the%20Irwin%20Amphitheatre%2C%20topped%20with%20cupolas%20above%20its%20main%20facade%2C%20was%20later%20redeveloped%20into%20the%20National%20Stadium.%20Its%20front%20lawns%20served%20as%20the%20venue%20of%20a%20National%20School%20Band%20Competition%20held%20ahead%20of%20the%2076th%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20on%20January%2024-25.%20PTI%20visited%20this%20historic%20landmark%20ahead%20of%20this%20year's%20celebrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20marble%20plaque%20installed%20on%20its%20wall%2C%20the%20Irwin%20amphitheatre%20was%20built%20in%201933%20as%20a%20gift%20from%20the%20then%20Maharaja%20of%20Bhavnagar%20who%20donated%20Rs%205%20lakh%20for%20its%20construction%20and%20was%20opened%20by%20the%20then%20viceroy%20Lord%20Willingdon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amphitheatre%20was%20named%20after%20the%20former%20Viceroy%20of%20India%2C%20Lord%20Irwin%2C%20who%20had%20inaugurated%20the%20new%20British%20capital%20New%20Delhi%20in%20February%201931%20during%20his%20viceroyalty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDesigned%20by%20Robert%20Torr%20Russell%2C%20also%20the%20architect%20of%20the%20iconic%20Connaught%20Place%20in%20central%20Delhi%2C%20the%20amphitheatre%20was%20renamed%20the%20National%20Stadium%20in%201951%20just%20before%20the%20Asian%20Games%20was%20hosted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20another%20plaque%20installed%20in%20another%20portion%20of%20the%20building%2C%20the%20foundation%20stone%20of%20the%20National%20Sports%20Stadium%20was%20laid%20by%20Pandit%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%20on%20January%2019%2C%201950%2C%20just%20a%20week%20before%20the%20first%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20were%20held%20at%20the%20venue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20the%20first%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%2C%20the%20over%20100-year-old%20Fauji%20Akhbar%20had%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20president%20drove%20out%20of%20the%20Government%20House%20(now%20Rashtrapati%20Bhavan)%20in%20state%20exactly%20at%202%3A30%20pm%20in%20a%2035-year-old%20coach%20specially%20renovated%20for%20the%20occasion%20bearing%20the%20new%20emblem%20of%20Asoka's%20capital%20and%20drawn%20by%20six%20sturdy%20Australian%20horses%2C%20at%20a%20slow%20trot%2C%20escorted%20by%20the%20president's%20bodyguard.%26quot%3B%20As%20the%20procession%20made%20its%20way%20through%20the%20Irwin%20Amphitheatre%2C%20chants%20of%20%26quot%3Bjai%26quot%3B%20echoed%20through%20the%20streets%20with%20cheers%20of%20people%20perched%20on%20trees%2C%20building%20roofs%20and%20every%20possible%20vantage%20point.%20The%20people's%20president%2C%20as%20he%20would%20come%20to%20be%20known%20later%20in%20his%20office%2C%20responded%20to%20the%20joyous%20greetings%20of%20the%20gathered%20masses%20with%20warmth%20and%20folded%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20drive%20ended%20exactly%20at%203%3A45%20pm%20at%20the%20Irwin%20Amphitheatre%20where%203%2C000%20officers%20and%20men%20of%20the%20three%20Armed%20Services%20of%20India%20and%20the%20police%20with%20massed%20bands%20had%20taken%20positions%20for%20the%20ceremonial%20parade%2C%26quot%3B%20reported%20the%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amphitheatre%2C%20housing%2015%2C000%20people%2C%20witnessed%20one%20of%20the%20most%20magnificent%20military%20parades%20in%20India's%20recent%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20venue%20was%20beautifully%20decked%20up%20and%20the%20stands%20were%20filled%20with%20people%20in%20their%20sartorial%20best.%20Seven%20massed%20bands%2C%20representing%20the%20three%20armed%20forces%20and%20the%20police%20regaled%20the%20spectators%2C%20while%20units%20of%20the%20forces%20and%20native%20contingents%20and%20regiments%20added%20colour%20and%20precision%20to%20the%20solemn%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737881820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fu2rsm10g_1950_625x300_26_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-1950-ex-indonesia-president-attended-1st-republic-day-parade-was-held-at-7561701%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20first%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations%20were%20held%20in%20the%201930s-era%20Irwin%20Amphitheatre%20in%201950.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fin-1950-ex-indonesia-president-attended-1st-republic-day-parade-was-held-at-7561701%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prashanth%20Prakash%20awarded%20Padma%20Shri%20for%20transforming%20startup%20ecosystem%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737881536000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fprashanth-prakash-awarded-padma-shri-for-transforming-startup-ecosystem-125012600364_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20founding%20partner%20of%20venture%20capital%20firm%20Accel%20India%2C%20Prakash%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20nurturing%20some%20of%20India's%20most%20iconic%20startups%2C%20including%20Flipkart%2C%20Swiggy%2C%20BookMyShow%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C